      • getComponentOrCurveOrSurface

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getComponentOrCurveOrSurface()
        Gets the value of the componentOrCurveOrSurface property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the componentOrCurveOrSurface property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getComponentOrCurveOrSurface().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list DrawingBorder PropertyBreak JAXBElement<Plane> JAXBElement<Ellipse> Text JAXBElement<CurveBoundedSurface> JAXBElement<Surface> PipeSlopeSymbol JAXBElement<Line> JAXBElement<CompositeCurve> JAXBElement<Shape> JAXBElement<BsplineSurface> Symbol JAXBElement<TrimmedCurve> GenericAttributes InsulationSymbol JAXBElement<Curve> JAXBElement<Circle> PipeFlowArrow JAXBElement<PolyLine> JAXBElement<BsplineCurve> Component Label ScopeBubble
